t":"@team-lead","targetColor":"red","summary":"UX review of Tasks 1-2, ready for Task 3","content":"Reviewed Tasks #1 and #2 after pulling latest (6fc51ca). UX assessment:\n\n**Task #1 (a11y error elements) -- looks good.** The always-in-DOM pattern is correct across login.html, todos.html, and edit_todo.html. Error elements are present but empty when no error, which means aria-describedby always resolves. No usability concerns.\n\n**Task #2 (Forgot password) -- mostly good, one small copy note:**\n- Link placement is correct -- between the form and \"Don't have an account?\" footer.\n- The \"Back to sign in\" link on the placeholder page is good.\n- The copy \"please try to remember your password or create a new account\" is a bit flippant. \"Try to remember your password\" comes across as dismissive. I'd suggest: \"Password reset isn't available yet. You can create a new account or try signing in again.\" But this is minor and doesn't block anything.\n\n**Ready for Task #3 review.** I've prepared focus management guidance for Carson's HTMX work -- sending that to him directly."}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"27dcb65e-8b82-4687-8068-433a01874c7f"}
{"parentUuid":"6e2a1716-12e9-4941-9c8a-e6c6fe329324","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/jwilger/projects/todo_list","sessionId":"3c280ca8-5969-4a2c-b8d2-e65e7a39442f","version":"2.1.37","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a718df2","slug":"agile-herding-corbato","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PCg2gvezXyhnuWTs1FHwQC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01SxBzfKrjgwSaWFJ1j6FhsZ","name":"SendMessage","input":{"type":"message","recipient":"carson-gross","content":"Carson, here's my UX guidance for Task #3 (HTMX progressive enhancement). These are the focus management and interaction details that matter most for usability:\n\n**Add todo:**\n- After successful add: clear the input, keep focus on the input field. This is the \"rapid entry\" pattern -- users adding multiple todos shouldn't have to click back into the field each time.\n- After validation error: keep focus on the input, show the error. Don't clear what they typed.\n\n**Toggle completion:**\n- No focus change needed. The button stays in place, the visual change (strikethrough + muted color) is the feedback. Keep it simple.\n\n**Delete:**\n- After confirming delete: focus should move to the next todo item in the list. If the deleted item was the last one, focus the previous item. If the list is now empty, focus the add input.\n- The empty state (\"No todos yet.\") should appear when the last item is deleted.\n\n**Edit (inline with HTMX):**\n- When entering edit mode: focus the title input immediately (the text field that replaces the title span).\n- After saving: focus should return to the item's title area.\n- After canceling: same -- focus back on the item.\n\n**General:**\n- The app must still work with JS disabled. HTMX enhances, doesn't replace.\n- After any swap, verify Tab order still makes sense. No orphaned focus.\n\nLet me know if you want to discuss any of these patterns.","summary":"UX focus management guidance for HTMX task"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":328,"cache_read_input_tokens":58193,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":328,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"}},"requestId":"req_011CXwL1cg8ar8U5zTv1uAkj","type":"assistant","uuid":"559e2535-1319-4ccd-9a0d-5d6dda924117","timestamp":"2026-02-08T21:41:27.188Z"}
{"parentUuid":"559e2535-1319-4ccd-9a0d-5d6dda924117","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/jwilger/projects/todo_list","sessionId":"3c280ca8-5969-4a2c-b8d2-e65e7a39442f","version":"2.1.37","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a718df2","slug":"agile-herding-corbato","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SxBzfKrjgwSaWFJ1j6FhsZ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"message\": \"Message sent to carson-gross's inbox\",\n  \"routing\": {\n    \"sender\": \"steve-krug\",\n    \"senderColor\": \"red\",\n    \"target\": \"@carson-gross\",\n    \"targetColor\": \"yellow\",\n    \"summary\": \"UX focus management guidance for HTMX task\",\n    \"content\": \"Carson, here's my UX guidance for Task #3 (HTMX progressive enhancement). These are the focus management and interaction details that matter most for usability:\\n\\n**Add todo:**\\n- After successful add: clear the input, keep focus on the input field. This is the \\\"rapid entry\\\" pattern -- users adding multiple todos shouldn't have to click back into the field each time.\\n- After validation error: keep focus on the input, show the error. Don't clear what they typed.\\n\\n**Toggle completion:**\\n- No focus change needed. The button stays in place, the visual change (strikethrough + muted color) is the feedback. Keep it simple.\\n\\n**Delete:**\\n- After confirming delete: focus should move to the next todo item in the list. If the deleted item was the last one, focus the previous item. If the list is now empty, focus the add input.\\n- The empty state (\\\"No todos yet.\\\") should appear when the last item is deleted.\\n\\n**Edit (inline with HTMX):**\\n- When entering edit mode: focus the title input immediately (the text field that replaces the title span).\\n- After saving: focus should return to the item's title area.\\n- After canceling: same -- focus back on the item.\\n\\n**General:**\\n- The app must still work with JS disabled. HTMX enhances, doesn't replace.\\n- After any swap, verify Tab order still makes sense. No orphaned focus.\\n\\nLet me know if you want to discuss any of these patterns.\"\n  }\n}"}]}]},"uuid":"37ed406a-d824-4319-93c9-66591cf3f271","timestamp":"2026-02-08T21:41:27.190Z","toolUseResult":{"success":true,"message":"Message sent to carson-gross's inbox","routing":{"sender":"steve-krug","senderColor":"red","target":"@carson-gross","targetColor":"yellow","summary":"UX focus management guidance for HTMX task","content":"Carson, here's my UX guidance for Task #3 (HTMX progressive enhancement). These are the focus management and interaction details that matter most for usability:\n\n**Add todo:**\n- After successful add: clear the input, keep focus on the input field. This is the \"rapid entry\" pattern -- users adding multiple todos shouldn't have to click back into the field each time.\n- After validation error: keep focus on the input, show the error. Don't clear what they typed.\n\n**Toggle completion:**\n- No focus change needed. The button stays in place, the visual change (strikethrough + muted color) is the feedback. Keep it simple.\n\n**Delete:**\n- After confirming delete: focus should move to the next todo item in the list. If the deleted item was the last one, focus the previous item. If the list is now empty, focus the add input.\n- The empty state (\"No todos yet.\") should appear when the last item is deleted.\n\n**Edit (inline with HTMX):**\n- When entering edit mode: focus the title input immediately (the text field that replaces the title span).\n- After saving: focus should return to the item's title area.\n- After canceling: same -- focus back on the item.\n\n**General:**\n- The app must still work with JS disabled. HTMX enhances, doesn't replace.\n- After any swap, verify Tab order still makes sense. No orphaned focus.\n\nLet me know if you want to discuss any of these patterns."}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"559e2535-1319-4ccd-9a0d-5d6dda924117"}
